The paper presents a motion control and planning framework for wheeled quadrupedal robots, which involves optimization and hierarchical whole-body control. This work is highly relevant to the field of robotics, specifically in the area of robot locomotion. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves optimization and control, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques for motion planning, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves image processing for terrain mapping, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
